Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.14,0:00:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Everyone, Kaleido Star is about to start.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.11,0:00:20.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When you watch Kaleido Star,\Nplease keep your room brightly lit,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.88,0:00:23.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and sit as far from the TV as you can.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.83,0:00:28.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Well, well, well. Do you know\Nsomeone among your friends{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.69,0:00:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}who likes to make everybody laugh?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.13,0:00:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Anna told me that her father used to\Nmake her laugh a lot when she was little.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.05,0:00:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But the father she met after not seeing\Nhim for a long time is completely different.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.91,0:00:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When something like this happens,\NI wonder if there is anything I can do.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.43,0:00:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder. I wonder.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.03,0:01:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What is it that you want to do? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.63,0:01:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Every time I was asked that {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.48,0:01:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I looked up at the blue sky {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.27,0:01:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The answer is only in my heart {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.57,0:01:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't easily say the\Nwords that are really important{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.10,0:01:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I start running towards\Nthe place the light points to{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.14,0:01:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's so much in my heart\Nthat I want to embrace, I could cry{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.30,0:01:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll keep painting my way,\NI promise, take it someday{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.24,0:01:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Beyond the horizon,\Nwhere the white clouds drift{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.29,0:02:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The future is lined up and\Nit'll always be there by my side{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.85,0:02:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna, you're the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.54,0:02:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Anna's Not So Amazing Father."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.44,0:02:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems your fans are coming\Nto see you every day, Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.28,0:03:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna, I think you should be a\Nlittle more sociable with your fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.93,0:03:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.62,0:03:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not good?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.66,0:03:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.86,0:03:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your fans will cry if they see you like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.21,0:03:12.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.40,0:03:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I still have a long way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.64,0:03:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Anna, why did you join Kaleido Stage?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.44,0:03:21.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you like to make people laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.17,0:03:24.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I love Kaleido Stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.93,0:03:27.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But of course, I love comedy too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.24,0:03:28.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.25,0:03:30.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, your dream is to make the\Naudience laugh at Kaleido Stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.94,0:03:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.60,0:03:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if it's your dream, Sora's\Nalready made it come true, right Sora?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.55,0:03:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.65,0:03:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.65,0:03:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The stand-up comedian Jack Barron\Nwill be at the Comedy Theater?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.56,0:03:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.56,0:03:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.43,0:03:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.70,0:03:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause I haven't seen him in ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.53,0:03:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean "haven't seen him"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.47,0:03:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.56,0:04:00.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.55,0:04:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, stop it, Bacchus! Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.97,0:04:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, give it back to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.58,0:04:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ribbit, ribbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.66,0:04:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Bacchus!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.13,0:04:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give Anna's shoe back, ribbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.74,0:04:19.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The thing I still remember is that he used to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.53,0:04:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,imitate frog or owl sounds to\Nmake me and my friends laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.43,0:04:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna, I need to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.23,0:04:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.78,0:04:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm... To tell you the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.13,0:04:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm an alien from the planet Jaga Imo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.74,0:04:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my name is "Jagaimo" jaga.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.82,0:04:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't hurry up, you won't have dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.18,0:04:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We got scolded, jaga.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.01,0:04:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, then, one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.92,0:04:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, Jack?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.67,0:04:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please understand, Julia.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.45,0:05:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.34,0:05:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I stay like this, I'll be ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.07,0:05:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.16,0:05:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.57,0:05:18.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.72,0:05:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please come back soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.77,0:05:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But after that, he never came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.41,0:05:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A talent agent who specialized\Nin comedians told Dad
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.91,0:05:37.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that he could get him\Ncast in a famous TV show.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.01,0:05:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... He's never been on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.77,0:05:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you hear this kind \Nof story all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.16,0:05:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since then, have you seen your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.43,0:05:46.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not even once.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.97,0:05:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sends a Christmas card once a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.72,0:05:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His address keeps changing,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.42,0:05:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so there's been no way for me to contact him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.00,0:05:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.35,0:05:59.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you have been checking\Nperformers at the Comedy Theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.11,0:06:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you never know when your\Nfather may perform at the Comedy Theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.14,0:06:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... That's sorta the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.09,0:06:08.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I truly love comedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.83,0:06:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, the Comedy Theater is close by! Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.73,0:06:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, in that case, we have to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.99,0:06:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I actually have a chance to meet him,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.65,0:06:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a part of me wants to, and\Nanother part of me is scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.20,0:06:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We shall accompany you, Your Highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.60,0:06:24.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.66,0:06:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't! Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.81,0:06:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you hear what I said?!\NDon't put your hand in my back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.46,0:06:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you doing?!\NTake your hand out of my back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.01,0:06:37.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna's father...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.48,0:06:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--I wonder if he'll notice Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.92,0:06:39.10,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hm? Did you say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.10,0:06:40.14,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--I'm hard of hearing nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.10,0:06:40.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Since he hasn't seen her for ten years,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.14,0:06:42.21,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--The thing getting harder \Nis not your hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.88,0:06:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--I'm sure he'll be surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.21,0:06:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it also getting harder\Nto go back home to your wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.67,0:06:48.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.59,0:06:50.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you thank them too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.15,0:06:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.36,0:06:57.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's my voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.34,0:07:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next up is a man who missed\Ntaking the world by storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.68,0:07:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jack Barron!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.42,0:07:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, please welcome him\Nwith a warm round of applause.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.67,0:07:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That old man's been using the\Nsame old material for the last 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.43,0:07:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that's changed is that he got\Nbald and the puppet got dentures.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.87,0:07:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the level of the audience went downhill.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.62,0:07:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.50,0:07:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys look like you're not having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.76,0:07:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you two are dating?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.57,0:07:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.58,0:07:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The girl you brought here\Nyesterday was better looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.93,0:07:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.99,0:07:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you, what the hell are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.42,0:07:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's lying. Lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.79,0:07:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.42,0:07:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're skinnier than the\Ngirl he brought here yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.95,0:07:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.12,0:08:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.64,0:08:09.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.34,0:08:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful on the way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.56,0:08:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.30,0:08:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy... Daddy...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.06,0:08:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.04,0:08:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Little Mermaid of Kaleido Stage is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.17,0:08:39.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.25,0:08:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Hello...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.35,0:08:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The girl who plays the Little Mermaid
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.44,0:08:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,looks more like a blowfish in a fashion show.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.16,0:08:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Little Mermaid is without\Na doubt a dreamlike story.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.05,0:08:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it a story of a blowfish girl\Nwho is trying to be a princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.41,0:09:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is... my dad?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.37,0:09:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is...? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.16,0:09:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna, you're cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.01,0:09:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Anna, your mom is waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.07,0:09:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.23,0:09:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I expect Kaleido Stage to turn\Ninto a seafood restaurant any day now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.25,0:09:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Anna!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.32,0:09:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna, wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.89,0:09:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like everyone's in a hurry today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.28,0:09:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it the basketball finals today?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.27,0:09:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like there's still a fan of\NJack Barron other than myself out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.75,0:10:00.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to New York with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.10,0:10:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make your family proud!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.91,0:10:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy... Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.77,0:10:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.07,0:10:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.55,0:10:20.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He fooled me. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.21,0:10:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was great.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.51,0:10:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A good job, Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.05,0:10:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to see that you're doing fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.21,0:10:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about yesterday, making you feel bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.17,0:10:42.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.24,0:10:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, what happened\Nwith your father after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.35,0:10:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.22,0:10:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's better not to see him anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.11,0:10:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What! Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.15,0:10:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jack Barron abandoned my mom\Nand me, and turned into another man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.54,0:11:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he wants\Nto see his daughter now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.67,0:11:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.76,0:11:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She still has a long way\Nto go to be a comedian.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.67,0:11:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we go there one more time?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.12,0:11:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.39,0:11:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.61,0:11:33.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.10,0:11:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.52,0:11:39.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.60,0:11:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.29,0:11:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do to Sora?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.25,0:11:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Policeman. It's not what you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.88,0:11:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this revenge for yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.34,0:11:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.52,0:12:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you ran away...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.97,0:12:04.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You came to see Anna, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.92,0:12:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just happened to be in the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.96,0:12:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna told me a story about her\Nfather from when she was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.17,0:12:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She told me that he was a nice\Nfather who made her laugh a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.89,0:12:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Even though he's an unpopular comedian\Nwho keeps making the audience mad."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.37,0:12:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that what she said?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.11,0:12:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.63,0:12:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in her\Nmeeting with a father like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.07,0:12:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must be thirsty from all that running.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.56,0:12:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.23,0:12:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.92,0:12:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how long will you be staying in town?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.95,0:12:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.94,0:12:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once I finish the evening\Nshow, I'm leaving town.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.31,0:12:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What! That soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.30,0:12:49.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, anyway, I was invited onstage because\Nthe owner of the theater felt pity for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.37,0:12:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It says, "Once again, a silly\Nperson somewhere around here
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.56,0:12:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is poking her nose into\Nsomething she should not."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.03,0:13:01.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.04,0:13:03.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember this card meant\Nsomething better than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.93,0:13:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like you've become a little wiser.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.36,0:13:09.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the reversed position of The Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.35,0:13:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It means that one will \Nacknowledge his faults,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.04,0:13:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and remove a misunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.41,0:13:14.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he can correct his course and\Npoint himself in the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.58,0:13:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a card for hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.11,0:13:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.01,0:13:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do my best so that Anna and\Nher dad can meet one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.95,0:13:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father told me that tomorrow\Nnight's show will be the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.16,0:13:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.01,0:13:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.01,0:13:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It shrunk...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.83,0:13:33.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Anna,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.15,0:13:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why don't you go see your father after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.53,0:13:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, maybe, I should...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.50,0:13:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.16,0:13:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should have eggs\Nsunny-side-up for breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.86,0:13:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.64,0:13:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your father said he'll be waiting\Nat the restaurant near the pier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.04,0:13:50.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.05,0:13:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora, her father is the talk of the cast.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.94,0:13:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.21,0:13:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it'd be better
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.74,0:14:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to just quietly keep an eye on how\Neverything turns out once in a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.41,0:14:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.79,0:14:12.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Barron...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.39,0:14:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.20,0:14:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you took the time to come here, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.71,0:14:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.06,0:14:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course she doesn't want to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.35,0:14:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.82,0:14:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.68,0:14:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I hadn't poked my nose into her business,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.69,0:14:33.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna might have come to see you on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.70,0:14:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna is lucky,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.53,0:14:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,having a nice friend like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.44,0:14:41.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... I don't know if I could\Nsay I'm doing this for Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.21,0:14:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.74,0:14:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost my parents in a car\Naccident when I was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.90,0:14:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.73,0:14:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought... Since Anna\Ncan still see her father,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.96,0:14:56.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she should meet him and talk\Nabout many things like she used to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.38,0:14:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.29,0:15:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm doing this not for Anna, but for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.88,0:15:06.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.91,0:15:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... What's wrong with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.48,0:15:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Little Mermaid, snap out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.28,0:15:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tears don't suit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.75,0:15:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Anna cried,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.41,0:15:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this always cheered her up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.79,0:15:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please bring a large serving of chocolate\Nchip ice cream to this little mermaid!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.27,0:15:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.21,0:15:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.62,0:15:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna? Are you doing all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.13,0:15:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. How about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.99,0:15:52.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just wondering what I should do\Nwith the window that Bacchus just broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.98,0:15:55.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.04,0:15:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.57,0:15:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I met Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.70,0:16:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What! Jack?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.12,0:16:04.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. At the Comedy Theater in Cape Mary.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.36,0:16:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Comedy Theater...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.14,0:16:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know the place?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.13,0:16:08.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.77,0:16:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I met your dad at that\NComedy Theater a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.75,0:16:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.63,0:16:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One day, an inexperienced new comedian
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.56,0:16:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,showed up to meet the owner, Bob.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.67,0:16:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From that evening, Jack appeared\Non stage at the Comedy Theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.15,0:16:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was warmhearted and funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.31,0:16:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he had an original personal technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.21,0:16:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He became very popular\Nat the theater in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.20,0:16:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before I knew it, I was\Nalso a big fan of Jack Barron.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.19,0:16:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he's different now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.52,0:16:46.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When a guy makes the audience\Nmad and gets a kick out of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.15,0:16:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't call him a comedian.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.53,0:16:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is the worst!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.85,0:16:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you tell Jack?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.37,0:16:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.56,0:16:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.64,0:16:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If what you said is true,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.96,0:17:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the only person who can save\Nthe current Jack Barron is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.50,0:17:03.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please give my best regards to Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.83,0:17:11.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.13,0:17:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next up is Jack Barron, whose\Nperformance here tonight will be his last.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.07,0:17:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do your best, Jack boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.36,0:17:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Anna didn't come after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.66,0:17:27.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They will have another chance to meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.54,0:17:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.90,0:17:33.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.60,0:17:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, the audience is still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.85,0:17:40.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's true that you can't see\Nthis kind of stupid ventriloquism on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.84,0:17:42.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.90,0:17:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wearing nice looking glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.44,0:17:47.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a matter of fact, I have some too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.69,0:17:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.37,0:17:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I wear this, I don't need\Nto see that girl's same old face.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.22,0:17:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.40,0:18:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... This again...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.51,0:18:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, look, look...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.70,0:18:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're chilling the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.76,0:18:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.33,0:18:14.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.33,0:18:15.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.77,0:18:17.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.63,0:18:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and your mom are exactly alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.19,0:18:23.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, of course, your mom\Nwas 30% prettier than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.27,0:18:28.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're such a comedian, why\Ndon't you make the audience laugh,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.77,0:18:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jack Barron?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.87,0:18:34.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or, are you just a {\i1}Junk {\i0}Baron now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.66,0:18:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Junk Baron Jack Barron.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.58,0:18:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is a perfect stage name for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.61,0:18:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say you would\Nmake it big in New York?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.65,0:18:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what are you doing in\Nthis shabby comedy house?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.22,0:18:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.79,0:18:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The agent who scouted me
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.21,0:18:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,said that he would help\Nme debut all over the U.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.20,0:18:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a very talented man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.26,0:19:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jack Barron abandoned his\Nfamily and followed that guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.24,0:19:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to that agent,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.02,0:19:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ended up going around to all of the\Ncomedy theaters in New York every day...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.89,0:19:08.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,trying to find a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.54,0:19:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.79,0:19:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to that talented agent?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.05,0:19:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was drinking every night...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.38,0:19:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with my money.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.51,0:19:17.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.73,0:19:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was rejected by all the\Ncomedy theaters in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.38,0:19:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, I was even rejected at a\Ndairy shop on the New Jersey state line.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.36,0:19:28.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, it was like the NYC \NMarathon out of season.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.82,0:19:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A month passed by, and when\NI came back to the cheap New York hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.96,0:19:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the agent, my money and\Nmy luggage were all gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.29,0:19:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like he was more\Ntalented in {\i1}that {\i0}kind of area.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.14,0:19:45.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you should have come back home!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.35,0:19:47.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell were you doing for ten years?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.98,0:19:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost my hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.77,0:19:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I kept looking for that hat...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.33,0:19:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in back alleys and underpasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.88,0:19:56.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I also used to search in the\Ntrash bins at the posh hotels.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.28,0:19:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ironically,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.80,0:20:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I realized,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.26,0:20:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when I finally came back to the\Nstage after so many years away...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.37,0:20:08.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.24,0:20:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one I want to make laugh...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.50,0:20:16.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one I want to make\Nlaugh one more time is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.41,0:20:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, why don't you make\Nme laugh like you used to...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.54,0:20:20.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a comedian, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.30,0:20:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make your darling daughter laugh, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.94,0:20:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Jack!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.74,0:20:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.12,0:20:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna, you're cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.15,0:20:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.55,0:20:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.36,0:20:58.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you cry with this,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.92,0:21:01.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.72,0:21:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.02,0:21:18.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.71,0:21:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you want to be my partner, Anna?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.31,0:21:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.19,0:21:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My current dream is right here, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.01,0:21:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.56,0:21:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.14,0:21:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm heading to a comedy theater in\NSt. Louis that Bob recommended me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.03,0:21:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll revive Jack Barron one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.54,0:21:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.65,0:22:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.65,0:22:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck, Daddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.06,0:22:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom said hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.82,0:22:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Then I'll be going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.35,0:22:22.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My father is Jack Barron. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.81,0:22:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Jack Barron I've \Nloved since I was little.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.23,0:22:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When you're lonely, what do you do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.91,0:22:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Never say you don't get any of that{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.25,0:22:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sleep, play, flip through a magazine{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.10,0:22:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When you're lonely, you're lonely{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.55,0:22:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Like always, invisible vibes fly\Naround the city today, tulututu{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.30,0:22:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Anyway, the vector of my heart\Nis talking about so many reasons{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.81,0:23:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to be free and fly the skies{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.65,0:23:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I don't have space to spread my wings{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.38,0:23:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I have faith {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.42,0:23:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There is a future yet to be shaped{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.16,0:23:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And there's a me that I want to shape{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.84,0:23:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if I'm sad, even if it's a mistake{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.30,0:23:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll do what I want and\Nfly towards the freedom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.68,0:23:36.68,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Next Kaleido Star"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.06,0:23:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why am I so concerned about that girl?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.27,0:23:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And so, once again, another ordeal.{\i0}
